VALUES ('3700054f-fa3f-42fe-97d0-85d25cb53f10', 'Which choice best characterizes the text''s rhetorical structure?', 'Educators reviewing literacy program 100080 concluded that students who discussed readings in pairs improved comprehension scores more than those who answered worksheets alone. Teachers in the pair-discussion classrooms reported that students referenced textual evidence when disagreeing, a behavior rarely observed during silent worksheet completion. Standardized pre- and post-tests showed a twelve-point average gain for the discussion cohort versus a four-point gain for the worksheet cohort over the same six-week unit. The educators emphasize that discussion prompts were structured—not unstructured chat—and required each partner to cite a line from the text. Yet practitioners now recognize that the phenomenon resists the single-cause explanation the passage first outlines.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It lists technical vocabulary from the opening sentences without showing how those terms support a cumulative argument across the full paragraph from mechanism to outcome overall here throughout overall in sum in context as","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."},{"id":"B","text":"It predicts that the author will publish a memoir, a motivation the passage never discusses or reasonably implies from its expository structure and academic tone in sum, in a way that matches how the.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Narrative Speculation] Imports unsupported assumptions about author motivation or future plans."},{"id":"C","text":"It claims effects are analyzed before causes are defined, inverting the passage''s movement from causal mechanism to documented outcome in the study described in context as written overall in sum in context as written.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Structural Inversion] Reverses the actual sequence of ideas the passage develops."},{"id":"D","text":"It establishes a cause-and-effect claim, supplies seasonal field evidence, and acknowledges limitations before drawing implications as written here throughout overall in sum in context as written in sum in context as written here","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (D). Correct (D). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."}]'::jsonb, 'D', 'Step 1 — Identify the passage organization
Focus on {{yellow:students}} in the passage. The structure item asks you to identify the passage organization before comparing choices.

Step 2 — Match structure to purpose
Compare each option against explicit textual evidence. On easy items, correct answers usually restate the passage faithfully without absolute words the text does not support.

Step 3 — Confirm the description
