VALUES ('26351408-18d0-4d37-ab8f-607cd570ccc8', 'Which choice best describes the overall structure of the text?', 'Historians examining trade route 100082 note that camel caravans carried not only goods but also astronomical tables, spreading navigation techniques across deserts long before printed maps existed. Recently, however, investigators published findings that complicate the long-standing consensus described above. Merchants who survived the crossing depended on star charts copied onto leather scrolls, and those copies often accumulated marginal notes from later travelers. A ledger recovered near route 100082 lists dates, caravan leaders, and the scientific texts exchanged at each oasis, suggesting that commerce and scholarship moved together. When one city tightened tariffs, caravans rerouted through secondary wells, and the astronomical knowledge rerouted with them. Modern', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It claims the author presents a legislative solution before defining the problem, reversing the sequence of argument the passage follows from theoretical model to empirical findings.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] [Structural Inversion] Reverses the actual sequence of ideas the passage develops."},{"id":"B","text":"It delineates a dominant framework, presents findings that qualify its applicability, and clarifies pragmatic policy implications as written here throughout overall in sum in context as written.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (B). Correct (B). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."},{"id":"C","text":"It summarizes the opening historical context without addressing the empirical challenge or the qualified defense that structures the passage''s conclusion in the final paragraphs here throughout.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Narrative Speculation] [Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."}