VALUES ('ea4d4831-4172-43f6-ae8f-ed887e6f8185', 'Which choice best describes the relationship between the text''s opening and its conclusion?', 'Historians examining trade route 100106 note that camel caravans carried not only goods but also astronomical tables, spreading navigation techniques across deserts long before printed maps existed. Merchants who survived the crossing depended on star charts copied onto leather scrolls, and those copies often accumulated marginal notes from later travelers. A ledger recovered near route 100106 lists dates, caravan leaders, and the scientific texts exchanged at each oasis, suggesting that commerce and scholarship moved together. When one city tightened tariffs, caravans rerouted through secondary wells, and the astronomical knowledge rerouted with them. Modern scholars therefore treat desert trade networks as early information highways rather than', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"It presents the counter-perspective as appearing before the consensus view, reversing the actual order of ideas in the text from established model to challenge in context.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Scope] [Structural Inversion] Reverses the actual sequence of ideas the passage develops."},{"id":"B","text":"It contrasts an earlier consensus with newer findings, reconciles partial agreement with dispute, and qualifies the scope of the conclusion as written here throughout overall in sum.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (B). Correct (B). This choice matches the passage''s rhetorical architecture from framework through evidence to qualified implications."},{"id":"C","text":"It accurately describes the concession in sentence two but ignores how the passage integrates that concession into a broader qualified defense in the closing sentences here.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Narrative Speculation] [Partial Scope] Describes only part of the passage, ignoring its overall trajectory."},{"id":"D","text":"It treats the author''s caution as evidence of personal indecision rather than as a deliberate rhetorical strategy the structure enacts throughout the paragraph throughout overall in sum.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Structural Inversion] [Narrative Speculation] Imports unsupported assumptions about author motivation or future plans."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Step 1 — Identify the passage organization
